{
  "text": "The amount of upper ocean thermal energy, hereafter referred to as the upper ocean heat content (UOHC, [CITATION_1] , is the primary energy source term for the development of hurricanes. The UOHC is determined by the temperature integrated from the surface to the depth of the 26\u00b0C isotherm (D26), i.e., UOHC\u00f0x; y\u00de \u00bc q o C p R sfc",
